</specimenCount>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="171" pageNumber="172" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="171.[151,1437,1187,1788]" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1403,1428]" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name means ‘living on 
<taxonomicName box="[677,750,1403,1428]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Erylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[677,750,1403,1428]" italics="true" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">Erylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’, referring to the fact the 
<typeStatus box="[1061,1159,1403,1428]" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">holotype</typeStatus>
encrusts a specimen of 
<taxonomicName box="[151,224,1439,1464]" class="Demospongiae" family="Geodiidae" genus="Erylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Astrophorida" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,224,1439,1464]" italics="true" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">Erylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="171" pageNumber="172" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="171.[151,1437,1187,1788]" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1475,1500]" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species differs from the two common 
<collectingRegion box="[882,964,1475,1500]" country="Sri Lanka" name="Central" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">Central</collectingRegion>
<collectingRegion box="[975,1030,1476,1499]" country="Tanzania" name="Mjini Magharibi" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">West</collectingRegion>
Atlantic species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1266,1397,1475,1500]" class="Demospongiae" family="Spirastrellidae" genus="Spirastrella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1266,1397,1475,1500]" italics="true" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">Spirastrella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Duchassaing &amp; Michelotti, 1864" authorityName="Duchassaing &amp; Michelotti" authorityYear="1864" class="Demospongiae" family="Spirastrellidae" genus="Spirastrella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="coccinea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">S. coccinea</emphasis>
(Duchassaing &amp; Michelotti, 1864)
</taxonomicName>
(as 
<taxonomicName authority="Duchassaing &amp; Michelotti, 1864" authorityName="Duchassaing &amp; Michelotti" authorityYear="1864" box="[731,838,1511,1536]" class="Demospongiae" family="Microcionidae" genus="Thalysias" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[731,838,1511,1536]" italics="true" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">Thalysias</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Verrill, 1907" authorityName="Verrill" authorityYear="1907" box="[916,1182,1511,1536]" class="Demospongiae" family="Spirastrellidae" genus="Spirastrella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="mollis">
<emphasis box="[916,1020,1511,1536]" italics="true" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">S. mollis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Verrill" box="[1034,1182,1511,1536]" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" refString="Verrill, A. E. (1907) The Bermuda Islands: Part V. An account of the Coral Reefs (Characteristic life of the Bermuda Coral Reefs). Porifera: Sponges. Transactions of the Connecticut Academy of Arts and Sciences, 12, 330 - 344." type="journal article" year="1907">Verrill, 1907</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(which was recently extensively described in 
<bibRefCitation author="Rutzler" box="[435,653,1547,1572]" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" refString="Rutzler, K., Piantoni, C., Van Soest, R. W. M. &amp; Diaz, M. C. (2014) Diversity of sponges (Porifera) from cryptic habitats on the Belize barrier reef near Carrie Bow Cay. Zootaxa, 3805 (1), 1 - 129. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3805.1.1" type="journal article" year="2014">
Rützler 
<emphasis box="[526,585,1547,1572]" italics="true" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
), in having very small compact spirasters only. The first of these, 
<taxonomicName class="Demospongiae" family="Spirastrellidae" genus="Spirastrella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="coccinea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">S. coccinea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, has spirasters up to 61 µm, the second, 
<taxonomicName box="[717,815,1583,1608]" class="Demospongiae" family="Spirastrellidae" genus="Spirastrella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="mollis">
<emphasis box="[717,815,1583,1608]" italics="true" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">S. mollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, up to 50 µm. Both show a clear division of large and small spirasters (
<typeStatus box="[346,407,1620,1644]" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">types</typeStatus>
1 and 
<quantity box="[492,539,1619,1644]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" unit="in" value="2.0">2 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation author="Rutzler" box="[549,769,1619,1644]" pageId="171" pageNumber="172" refString="Rutzler, K., Piantoni, C., Van Soest, R. W. M. &amp; Diaz, M. C. (2014) Diversity of sponges (Porifera) from cryptic habitats on the Belize barrier reef near Carrie Bow Cay. Zootaxa, 3805 (1), 1 - 129. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3805.1.1" type="journal article" year="2014">
Rützler 
<emphasis box="[641,701,1619,1644]" italics="true" pageId="171" pageNumber="172">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
) with, in the larger spirasters, 2 spiral turns, whereas the microscleres in the new species described here have a more continuous variation, and are generally more compact showing 1–1.5 (rarely 2) spiral turns only. Detailed shapes are also clearly different among all three species. Tylostyles in the present new species exceed these of the other two in length (up to 822 µm vs. 680 and 520 respectively).
</paragraph>
